t versions = testedVersions(entries);\\n./docs/support/index.html:694:          const versions = testedVersions(normalizedEntries);\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:52:- Validation of `index.json` schema and `metadata-version`/`tested-versions` integrity.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:61:GitHub Actions, configured by [`ci.json`](../ci.json) as the single source of truth for OS/JDK matrix, run the workflows enumerated in [CI.md](CI.md):\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:62:- PR-scoped: changed-metadata, changed-infrastructure, new-library-version, Spring AOT smoke, library-stats validation, library-and-framework-list validation, checkstyle.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:137:    NBT->>NBT: for each application dependency,<br/>pick metadata version via index.json<br/>(tested-versions → default-for → latest)\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:161:**2. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/index.json`** — one per supported artifact, schema [metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json](../metadata/schemas/metadata-library-index-schema-v2.1.0.json). It is a JSON **array** of entries. Metadata entries require `metadata-version`, `tested-versions`, and `allowed-packages`, with optional `default-for` (Java regex), `latest: true`, `override: true`, `requires: [\\\"<group>:<artifact>\\\", …]`, `test-version`, `skipped-versions`, `language`, and the four URL fields. An index can alternatively contain a single `not-for-native-image: true` marker with a reason. Plugin-relevant fields are the first six.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:169:1. `v ∈ tested-versions` → use that entry's `metadata-version` directory directly.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:177:    LoadIndex --> Tested{\\\"Any entry with<br/><code>v ∈ tested-versions</code>?\\\"}\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:206:- **FR-M-6** Exactly one entry in a non-empty `index.json` must carry `latest: true`. If a library version is not in `tested-versions`, the harness selects an entry by matching the optional `default-for` regex.\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:216:- **FR-T-6** Newly added `tested-versions` entries are recorded in `index.json` only after they pass on **every** required environment (enforced by `verify-new-library-version-compatibility`).\\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:235:- **FR-CI-4** The Spring AOT smoke matrix runs only when `metadata/` changes affect a Spring AOT project.\\n./docs/CI.md:16:The test matrix definition starts with [ci.json](../ci.json):\\n./docs/CI.md:25:  - Uses: generateMatrixBatchedCoordinates to build a matrix (java + os). Runs full tests, pulls only allowed Docker images, then disables Docker networking for deterministic runs.\\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, includes newly added tested versions from artifact-level index diffs, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\\n./docs/CI.md:34:  - Uses: generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix to compute impacted Spring AOT projects and produce a matrix; runs triaged native tests via [.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh).\\n./docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment